properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 9 at 3:48AM CST until February 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...HEAVY SNOW EXPECTED ACROSS CENTRAL AND EAST-CENTRAL WISCONSIN
TODAY...

.A low pressure system located over extreme southeast South Dakota
early this morning will track to northeast Iowa by noon, then
along the Wisconsin/Illinois border this afternoon. This is a
rather compact but vigorous storm system, and will bring a
significant snowfall to all but far northern Wisconsin. The storm
is also fast moving, so snow will quickly overspread the area
during the morning, but also diminish quickly from west to east
during the late afternoon and evening.

Although winds are not expected to be strong during the storm, the
heavy snowfall could reduce the visibility to under 1/4 mile at
times, especially in central and east-central Wisconsin. This will
likely result in hazardous travel conditions. Air travel is also
likely to be affected by the storm.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches.

* WHERE...Northern Marinette County, Florence, Southern
Marinette County and Northern Oconto County Counties.

* WHEN...From 9 AM this morning to 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Travel will become hazardous.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow is expected to develop between 800 am
and 1100 am, and the intensity of the snow will increase
quickly. This will result in rapidly deteriorating travel
conditions during the late morning.
properties.instruction:
If traveling today, expect to encounter roads that are snow
covered and slippery, and allow plenty of time to reach your
destination. The latest road conditions can be obtained by
calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THIS MORNING TO 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
